The Egypt Petroleum Show (EGYPS) is returning to Cairo in its second edition from 12 – 14 February 2018. It brings together the Egyptian and North African government representatives, key project owners, NOCs, IOCs, international service providers, EPC contractors, consultants and financiers to address the evolving opportunities in the Egyptian and North African energy arena. EGYPS 2018 provides the opportunity to gain insights into the upcoming oil and gas opportunities in Egypt and North Africa, from new regulations, investment opportunities, project requirements to short and long term strategic plans and priorities that will help form strategic partnerships and enhance industry collaboration in the region.